**WARN: (TCLCMD-1131):	'Command 'report_annotations' is obsolete and has been replaced with 'report_annotated_parasitics' and 'report_annotated_delay'. The obsolete command still works in this release, but to avoid this warning, and to ensure compatibility with future releases, update your scripts to use 'report_annotated_parasitics' and 'report_annotated_delay''

Usage: report_annotations [-help] [-ignore_floating_nets]
                          [-ignore_tied_low_high_net_arcs]
                          [-ignore_tied_low_high_nets] [-list_annotated]
                          [-list_non_annotated] [-max_missing <integer>]
                          [-missing_capacitances] [-missing_delays]
                          [-missing_rc] [-missing_resistances] [-missing_spf]
                          [-tcl_list] [-view <viewName>] [> <filename>]

-help                              # Prints out the command usage
-ignore_floating_nets              # Ignores nets without drivers, power, and
                                   # ground nets (bool, optional)
-ignore_tied_low_high_net_arcs     # Ignores timing arcs of power and ground
                                   # nets (bool, optional)
-ignore_tied_low_high_nets         # Ignores nets connected to tied_low and
                                   # tied_high cells (bool, optional)
-list_annotated                    # Lists detailed annotation information for
                                   # the following annotated arcs (bool, optional)
-list_non_annotated                # Lists the arc information for the
                                   # non-annotated arcs corresponding to the
                                   # following types of arcs (bool, optional)
-max_missing <integer>             # Limits the number of missing annotations
                                   # to the number specified (int, optional)
-missing_capacitances              # Reports the nets that are missing
                                   # capacitances (bool, optional)
-missing_delays                    # Reports the arcs that are missing SDF
                                   # annotations (bool, optional)
-missing_rc                        # Reports the nets that are missing
                                   # resistances and capacitances (bool, optional)
-missing_resistances               # Reports the nets that are missing
                                   # resistances (bool, optional)
-missing_spf                       # Reports the nets that are missing SPF data
                                   # (bool, optional)
-tcl_list                          # Produces the report in Tcl list format
                                   # instead of a tabular format (bool, optional)
-view <viewName>                   # Reports the coverage of annotations for
                                   # the specified analysis view
                                   # (string, optional)
> <filename>                       # Writes the report to the specified file
                                   # name. If the file already exists, the
                                   # software overwrites it
                                   # (redirect_operator, optional)